 </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Physically Challenged</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">15</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">12</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">RM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Young Talent</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">16</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">10</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">RM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Group (Traditional)</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">8</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">30</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">RM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Group (Contemporary)</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">8</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">25</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">RM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">International Group</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">12</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">20</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">RM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Maharis Style (Solo)</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">4</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">12</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">LM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Maharis &#160;Style (Group)</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">2</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">20</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">LM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr class=\"c25\">\r\n      <td class=\"c39\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Gotipuas (Group)</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c34\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">3</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c23\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Selected</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c29\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">20</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n      <td class=\"c17\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">LM</span> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;*Note- The artiste can dance two items but not to exceed 25 minutes.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c38\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2 c26\"><strong>Style vs. Dance</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160; – In the past, the International Odissi Festivals have scheduled choreography based on the styles or heritage of a renowned guru. &#160;Basically, the students and followers have adapted a particular techniques to express a particular repertoire. &#160;It has become an issue for an organizer like IPAP to see that we respect all the styles by keeping numbers of opportunities at the same level. &#160;It was also noticed that on an international stages Odissi is perceived as an Indian Classical Dance not as an Indian Classical Odissi of any particular style.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c7 c22\"><span class=\"c3\">In order to be more competitive and united as a group – we must not bring division among ourselves by calling or pointing any particular dance style incorrect, defective, better or worse. &#160;Overall, the dance is called Odissi irrespective of its style !</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c7 c22\"><span class=\"c14 c3\">Therefore, the 4</span> <span class=\"c3 c10\">th</span> <span class=\"c14 c3\">&#160;International Dance Festival will judge the artiste\'s caliber based on the overall presentation not on particular any techniques or followings.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"c7 c22\"><span class=\"c2 c26\"><strong>Quality is the ONLY criteria</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160; - This time all the applicants will be evaluated based on the recent video presentations irrespective of their background except the \"</span> <span class=\"c2\">Senior (Female)\", </span> <span class=\"c3\">\"</span> <span class=\"c2\">Established\", Senior(Male) </span> <span class=\"c3\">categories. &#160;These </span> <span class=\"c2 c26\">three</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;categories have proven records of their sustained dedications to the field of Odissi.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c3\">Dancers who have been recognized on a national and international standards will be invited automatically to the festival. &#160;For example artists recognized by both Government of India, or a reputable dance organizations may be considered. &#160;Senior Females, &#160;Established Females, Senior Males are the dancers who have been recommended and by organizations like Sangeet Natak Academy, India Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR) or on their panel, their past foreign tours, performing in recent &#160;acclaimed dance festivals, participating in workshops, seminars etc. </span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2\">Promising</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;is the </span> <span class=\"c2 c26\">most challenging</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;category of the festival where young dancers are trying to make a debut into a prospective established dancer category. &#160;They\'re the future of the Odissi dance and they have the potentials. &#160;A continuous performance track records, critic\'s comments, current video presentation, and strong recommendations by few gurus or esteemed dancers will be required to select a dancer into any categories..</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2 c14\"><strong>Young Prodigy</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;– A new category for very talented dancer under 5-15 will be included in this category. &#160;In past this category was not accepted due to </span> <span class=\"c14 c3\">their age, but in the 21</span> <span class=\"c10 c3\">st</span> <span class=\"c14 c3\">&#160;century the talent counts more than the age. &#160;The selection of this group would be by the Board.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><strong><span class=\"c2 c14\">International Dance</span> </strong>\r\n<span class=\"c3\">&#160;– Since Odissi is crossing &#160;over the five continents &#160;and seven oceans – there is a galaxy of international schools all over the world. &#160;In the past Odissi made North America as its second home. &#160;From its strong hold in Europe, Odissi has spread to Russia, &#160;China, Japan, Australia, Brazil, Argentina, Columbia etc. &#160; A One day event in the International Odissi Festival is not enough to accommodate all. &#160;Accordingly, the Board has decided to dedicate two full days for International Odissi Dancers by dividing them based on East Hemisphere and West Hemispere. &#160;Artistes will present solos and schools will present group repertoire.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><span class=\"c2 c14\"><strong>Purusha Anga</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;or Male dancers are another area where the male dancers have risen up to establish themselves in a distinct male form of choreography. &#160;Male are expressing the male postures and expressions. Purusha Anga has the categories of both Established and Promising.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c38\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2 c14\"><strong>Odissi Duets</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;is also a very popular dance form mostly male and female dancers presenting a pure dance form of Odissi repertoire.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c22\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2 c14\"><strong>Physically challenged</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;category will be presenting some of the true artistic perseverance and dedication towards the art form irrespective of limited physical cooperation.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c38\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2 c14\"><strong>Odissi Goups</strong>\r\n</span> <span class=\"c3\">&#160;both in Traditional and Contemporary dances will be presented both by national and international groups in the evening.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c38\"><strong><span class=\"c2 c14\">Maharis Style</span> <span class=\"c2\">:</span>\r\n</strong><span class=\"c2\"> &#160;</span> <span class=\"c3\">The festival will make a journey of Odissi. &#160;Without the Maharis the journey is not complete. &#160;Even though, there is no Maharis exist to perform, but there has been an effort by few Maharis School to preserve and demonstrate the typical art form.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"c4 c38\"><span class=\"c3\"></span> <span class=\"c2\"><strong>Gotipuas:</strong> &#160;</span> <span class=\"c3\">The real contribution of Gotipuas to the pure Odissi repertoire is immense. &#160;Therefore, the journey will continue from Maharis to Gotipuas and to Odissi.</span> </p>',0,'2011-07-29 02:39:19','2011-08-01 00:59:01'),(15,8,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:39:19','2011-08-01 00:59:01'),(16,9,'Body','<p>IPAP will start seminars on the following topics.</p>\r\n<ul><li>Protecting the Intellectual Property of Odissi Dance &amp; Music</li>\r\n<li>Enhancing Odissi in the 21st Century Stage</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'2011-07-29 02:47:22','2011-07-29 02:47:22'),(17,9,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:47:22','2011-07-29 02:47:22'),(18,10,'Body','<ul><li>Preventing against Physical Injuries/Physical Therapies</li>\r\n<li>Fit to dance - Diet &amp; Exercise</li>\r\n<li>Yoga in Odissi</li>\r\n<li>Art of Make-up</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'2011-07-29 02:47:57','2011-07-29 02:47:57'),(19,10,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:47:57','2011-07-29 02:47:57'),(20,11,'Body','<p>There will be a Field Tour to Konark Sun Temple with a stop-over at Konark Natya Mandap (only for Foreign participants)</p>',0,'2011-07-29 02:48:16','2011-07-29 02:48:16'),(21,11,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:48:16','2011-07-29 02:48:16'),(22,12,'Body','<p>IPAP is exploring the possibilities of few exhibits during the International Odissi Dance Festivals.  They are:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Photo Exhibits of famous dancers Avinash Pasricha</li>\r\n<li>Odissi Heritage Sand Statues by Sudarshan Patnaik</li>\r\n<li>Odissi  Journey by Ramakant Jena &amp; Soubhagya Pathy</li>\r\n<li>Odissi  jewelries</li>\r\n<li>Odissi Haata ( shops for dance related sales)   </li>\r\n</ul>',0,'2011-07-29 02:48:49','2011-07-29 02:48:49'),(23,12,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:48:49','2011-07-29 02:48:49'),(24,13,'Body','<p>Again the IPAP will be recognizing various individuals  at the Inaugural Ceremony based upon their contributions to Odissi to sustain and maintain its predominance in the field of Indian Classical Dance.  Various categories are:</p>\r\n<ul><li>Dancer</li>\r\n<li>Guru</li>\r\n<li>Musician</li>\r\n<li>Scholar</li>\r\n<li>Institution (Domestic)</li>\r\n<li>Institution (Foreign)</li>\r\n<li>Promoter</li>\r\n<li>Special Recognition</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'2011-07-29 02:49:46','2011-07-29 02:49:46'),(25,13,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:49:46','2011-07-29 02:49:46'),(26,14,'Body','<p>The IPAP Board has decided to invite Smt. Pratibha Patil, President of India to inaugurate the 4th International Festival at the Indira Gandhi Indoor Stadium at Cuttack at the event of Guinness Book of Records performing Largest Odissi Dance event being performed on December 23, 2011.</p>',0,'2011-07-29 02:50:12','2011-07-29 02:50:54'),(27,14,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:50:12','2011-07-29 02:50:54'),(28,15,'Body','<p>The festival is going invite  at least three dignitaries  each day.  There invitees could Union or State Ministers, Highly regarded cultural persons, journalists, or recognized artists. The Finale day be will be concluded by the Governor or the Chief Minister of Orissa. </p>',0,'2011-07-29 02:50:41','2011-07-29 02:51:16'),(29,15,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 02:50:41','2011-07-29 02:51:16'),(30,16,'Body','<p>The IPAP Board is consists of founding members and newly recruited members for  a limited term. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Chief Executive Office &amp; President of the Board</h3>\r\nPratap Das\r\n\r\n<h3> Founding Members </h3>\r\n<p>\r\nLate Arun Das, Anu Biswal and Ajaya Agrawalla are the founding members. \r\n</p>\r\n<h3>Board members</h3> \r\n<ul><li>Purna Patnaik</li>\r\n<li>Devi Prasad Mishra</li>\r\n<li>Brajendra Nath Sahu</li>\r\n<li>Bidhu Bhusana Mohanty</li>\r\n<li>Sitakantha Dash</li>\r\n<li>Shivraj Kanungo</li>\r\n<li>Ratna Roy</li>\r\n<li>Sukanya Mukerjee</li>\r\n<li>Chitra Krishnamurti</li>\r\n<li>Niharika Mohanty</li>\r\n<li>Niranjan Tripathy</li>\r\n<li>Santanu Das</li>\r\n<li>Tapan Padhi</li>\r\n<li>Neelamadhab Patro</li>\r\n<li>Devdutta Dash</li>\r\n<li>Saroj Mohanty – Treasurer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',0,'2011-07-29 03:00:51','2011-07-29 03:06:14'),(31,16,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:00:51','2011-07-29 03:06:14'),(32,17,'Body','<p>The Board has appointed a Planning &amp; Advisory Committee under the Chairmanship of Honorable Lalit Mansingh.  The other notable members are:<br />•	Dr. Minati Mishra<br />•	Padmabibhusana Sonal Mansingh<br />•	Padmashree Pandit Raghunath Panigrahi<br />•	Padmashree Sunil Kothari<br />•	Padmashree Madhavi Mudgal<br />•	Padmashree Ranjana Gauhar<br />•	Padmashree Kum Kum Mohanty<br />•	Padmashree Priyambada Hajmadi<br />•	Padmashree Kiron Segal<br />•	Santanu Mohapatra<br />•	Kshirod Chandra Mohanty<br />•	Ramahari  Das</p>',0,'2011-07-29 03:01:43','2011-07-29 03:01:43'),(33,17,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:01:43','2011-07-29 03:01:43'),(34,18,'Body','<p>IPAP has appointed a Logistics Committee to take care of the Technical, logistics, and the planning towards the execution of the festival.</p>\r\n<ul><li>Aruna Mohanty                                                                                                                                                                                      </li>\r\n<li>Sangita Gosain</li>\r\n<li>Guru Banamali Maharana</li>\r\n<li>Guru Dhaneswar Swain</li>\r\n<li>Shyamahari Chakra</li>\r\n<li>Sharmila Biswas</li>\r\n<li>Ratikanta Mohapatra</li>\r\n<li>Joydev Das </li>\r\n<li>Pramod Mohapatra</li>\r\n<li>Dinanath Pathy</li>\r\n<li>Soubhagya Pathy</li>\r\n<li>Ramakanta Jena</li>\r\n<li>Jyoti Ranjan Swain</li>\r\n<li>Bichitrananda Swain</li>\r\n<li>Manaranjan Pradhan</li>\r\n<li>Rahul Acharya</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'2011-07-29 03:03:23','2011-07-29 03:03:23'),(35,18,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:03:23','2011-07-29 03:03:23'),(36,19,'Body','<p>Member for all the Organization committees are being finalized.&#160; Check the individual pages for current tentative members.</p>\r\n<br />',0,'2011-07-29 03:03:46','2011-07-31 20:33:53'),(37,19,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:03:46','2011-07-31 20:33:53'),(38,20,'Body','',0,'2011-07-29 03:07:09','2011-07-29 03:07:09'),(39,20,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:07:09','2011-07-29 03:07:09'),(40,21,'Body','<p>Unlike the 3rd International Odissi Festival, IPAP can’t guarantee any fee for any categories of artists.  It’s our strong belief that we will make a strong appeal to the Government of India and our sponsors to fund the fees to our artists.</p>',0,'2011-07-29 03:07:51','2011-07-29 03:07:51'),(41,21,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:07:51','2011-07-29 03:07:51'),(42,22,'Body','<p>IPAP shall provide the boarding and lodging to the invited categories such as Seniors, Established Females, Senior males, Scholars, Paper presenters, invited critics, invited writers, invited event management personnel, experts, exhibitors and award winners etc. All the boarding are limited to two days only for participants.  Housing facilities shall not be provided to locals or resident of Cuttack/Bhubaneswar/Puri.</p>\r\n<p>Refreshments or food shall be provided to the participants of particular sessions or day only.</p>',0,'2011-07-29 03:08:10','2011-07-29 03:08:10'),(43,22,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:08:10','2011-07-29 03:08:10'),(44,23,'Body','<p>A transportation Fees will be allocated to the school.  It is the responsibilities of the artist to report at the dancing venue as asked to report.  There will be an occasional requirement of transportation to dance arena.  There will be a special  announcement for that.</p>',0,'2011-07-29 03:08:25','2011-07-29 03:08:25'),(45,23,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:08:25','2011-07-29 03:08:25'),(46,24,'Body','<p>Konark Temple Visit will be provided by IPAP for the pre-registered international artists and scholars.  Lunch will be provided at Konark Dance Academy.</p>',0,'2011-07-29 03:08:40','2011-07-29 03:08:40'),(47,24,'Side Body','',1,'2011-07-29 03:08:40','2011-07-29 03:08:40'),(48,25,'Body','<p>Except the Seniors Females, Established, Senior Males group all the rest of the categories must apply to </p>\r\n<p>IPAP,Post Box. 23018, Washington DC 20026 before September 30, 2011.  A screening and final selection will be done by IPAP.  The selection of artists for all 15 categories will be announced by October 1, 2011.</p>\r\n<p>Registration fees are not returnable irrespective of selection. All the applicants must send three copies of the DVD (10 minutes) , 2/3 recommendation, a small bio-data and a completed IPAP Registration form.  Previous dancers of IPAP Festivals have no guarantees of being selected.  Each category shall select the best entries of applicants irrespective of style, seniority, institution, gurus etc.  Selection of the categories can’t  be challenged.</p>\r\n<p>Applicants of Indian origin must send certified bank check payable to IPAP. Applicants from America must submit checks or money orders payable to IPAP.  Foreign applicants  must send  money order payable in  equivalent United States Dollars.  No checks shall be accepted from foreign national except United States and India.  But all checks shall be certified payable to IPAP.<br /> </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;font-size:1.25em;\">Please check here later for information about how to register.</p>\r\n<p>Fee for the Registration are as follows:</p>\r\n<table class=\"c5\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tbody><tr class=\"c25 heading\"><td class=\"c35\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Category</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c32\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Dead Line </span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Fee</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c36\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Post </span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Dead-Line</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Fee</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"c25\"><td class=\"c35\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">India (Solo)</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c32\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October 1</span>\r\n<span class=\"c11 c3\">st</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Rs.5000</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c36\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October 15th</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Rs. 7,500</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"c25\"><td class=\"c35\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">India (Group)</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c32\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October &#160;1</span>\r\n<span class=\"c11 c3\">st</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Rs. 10,000</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c36\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October 15</span>\r\n<span class=\"c11 c3\">th</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">Rs. 15,000</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c3\"></span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"c25\"><td class=\"c35\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">World (Solo)</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c32\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October 1</span>\r\n<span class=\"c11 c3\">st</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">$200</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c36\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">October 15</span>\r\n<span class=\"c3 c11\">th</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"c43\"><p class=\"c7\"><span class=\"c3\">$300</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"c25\"><td class=\"